Maintenance Culture Improvement & PM Transformation Plan
1. Problem Statement (Current State)
Key Issues Identified

Tool storage & shelves

Poor organization, no ownership

Time wasted searching for tools

Duplicate purchases & missing tools

Preventive Maintenance (PM) execution

PMs are too broad (entire press at once)

Inspections rushed or skipped due to time pressure

Findings are not consistently captured or actioned

PM + Repairs conflict

Inspections and repairs attempted at the same time

Leads to incomplete inspections and reactive work

No proper planning window

Understaffing reality

PM scope does not match available manpower

Technicians forced into firefighting mode

2. Vision & Objectives (Future State)
Maintenance Vision

Shift from reactive firefighting to planned, equipment-focused maintenance driven by data, ownership, and preparation.

Objectives

Reduce unplanned downtime

Improve PM quality and consistency

Make maintenance work visible, planned, and achievable

Build technician ownership and pride

Improve safety and efficiency

